I had been wondering if the nearby ephemeral pond could be suitable habitat for small-mouthed salamanders, and conditions were just right (55 degrees Fahrenheit overcast and heavy rains the day before) to find this individual under a log. Some interesting behaviors I saw from this individual were lifting up and wagging its tail in the air and producing a little chirp sound. Last picture is as flipped

Tried to flip the boards at the other spot but had no luck, so I came to the River Legacy trail and found this under a piece of plastic barrier near the Snider Creek bridge. There seemed to be some skin impairing vision in its left eye (do amphibians also get stuck shed?)
